    "schema_version": "3",
    "note": "Aave V3 Pool.swapBorrowRateMode(asset, interestRateMode). Per the legacy Aave V3 IPool NatSpec the interestRateMode arg is 'The current interest rate mode of the position being swapped: 1 for Stable, 2 for Variable' — i.e. the mode being swapped FROM. BorrowLogic.executeSwapBorrowRateMode burns the named-mode debt and mints the OTHER mode, so SwapRateModeAction.new_mode (the mode AFTER the swap) is the COMPLEMENT of the arg: arg 1 (STABLE) -> new_mode variable; arg 2 (VARIABLE) -> new_mode stable. Mainnet Pool v3.4+ no longer exposes this selector, so chain 1 is intentionally absent from this manifest and enforced by surface/aave/pool-mainnet.",
